<subSubSection id="2AC3655CFFA42449FCB2FBC30A580603" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="626636D7FFA42449FCB2FBC30A580603" blockId="13.[785,1378,877,1305]" lastBlockId="13.[168,1379,1319,3470]" pageId="13" pageNumber="298">
While examining specimens of purported 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FCB1FBAB0B46051F" authorityName="Spencer" authorityYear="1896" box="[786,1038,1114,1147]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Phascogale" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macdonnellensis">P. macdonnellensis</taxonomicName>
in collections of the Western Australian Museum, D. J. Kitchener and N. Caputi found dental variations consistent with a new species that occurred in close geographical proximity to 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FF75FAD60E800424" authorityName="Spencer" authorityYear="1896" box="[214,456,1319,1344]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Phascogale" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macdonnellensis">P. macdonnellensis</taxonomicName>
at Woodstock Station, 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FCBBFAD60C340424" box="[792,892,1319,1344]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Pilbara" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Pilbara</taxonomicName>
. They named this species 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FB5DFAD60FA20403" authorityName="Kitchener &amp; Caputi" authorityYear="1988" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Pseudantechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="woolleyae">P. woolleyae</taxonomicName>
in honor of dasyurid reproductive biologist P. A. Woolley. There are currently six recognized species of dasyurid marsupial 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FC8CFA9C0B4D04EA" authorityName="Tate" authorityYear="1947" box="[815,1029,1389,1422]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Pseudantechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudantechinus</taxonomicName>
, or “false antechinuses”: 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FF0CFA640E4B04D2" authorityName="Johnson" authorityYear="1954" box="[175,259,1429,1462]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Antechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bilarni">bilarni</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FEB7FA640EA904D2" authorityName="Spencer" authorityYear="1896" box="[276,481,1429,1462]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Phascogale" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macdonnellensis">macdonnellensis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FE53FA640D1604D2" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1906" box="[496,606,1429,1462]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Phascogale" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mimulus">mimulus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FDCCFA640DA804D2" box="[623,736,1429,1462]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Pseudantechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ningbing">ningbing</taxonomicName>
, rory:, and 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FCD5FA640CA104D2" authorityName="Kitchener &amp; Caputi" authorityYear="1988" box="[886,1001,1429,1462]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Pseudantechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="woolleyae">woolleyae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FC5AFA640B8E04D2" authorityName="Spencer" authorityYear="1896" box="[1017,1222,1429,1462]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Phascogale" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macdonnellensis">macdonnellensis</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FAB1FA640F9B04B9" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1906" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Phascogale" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mimulus">mimulus</taxonomicName>
were both initially placed in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FD5FFA4D0CC504B9" box="[764,909,1468,1501]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Antechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Antechinus</taxonomicName>
, along with 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FB9BFA4D0A1204B9" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[1080,1370,1468,1501]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Parantechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="apicalis">Parantechinus apicalis</taxonomicName>
. G. H. H. Tate in 1947 erected a new genus, 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FC97FA1D0B420761" authorityName="Tate" authorityYear="1947" box="[820,1034,1516,1541]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Pseudantechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudantechinus</taxonomicName>
, for 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FBF6FA1D0A690761" authorityName="Spencer" authorityYear="1896" box="[1109,1313,1516,1541]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Phascogale" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macdonnellensis">macdonnellensis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FF0CF9FA0E560748" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1906" box="[175,286,1547,1580]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Phascogale" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mimulus">mimulus</taxonomicName>
and a monotypic genus, 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FD24F9FA0C080748" box="[647,832,1547,1580]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Parantechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Parantechinus</taxonomicName>
, for 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FC24F9FA0CA00748" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[903,1000,1547,1580]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Parantechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="apicalis">apicalis</taxonomicName>
. W. D. L. Ride dismantled these in 1964 and returned all three species to 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FCF6F9C30CAE0737" box="[853,998,1586,1619]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Antechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Antechinus</taxonomicName>
. Woolley examined penile morphology of Ride’s 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FE4AF9A80D32071E" box="[489,634,1625,1658]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Antechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Antechinus</taxonomicName>
supergroup and proposed that 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FBE0F9A80A47071E" authorityName="Spencer" authorityYear="1896" box="[1091,1295,1625,1658]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Phascogale" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macdonnellensis">macdonnellensis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FA82F9A80F8007C6" authorityName="Johnson" authorityYear="1954" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Antechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bilarni">bilarni</taxonomicName>
, the undescribed “ 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FE71F9700D0D07C6" box="[466,581,1665,1698]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Pseudantechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ningbing">ningbing</taxonomicName>
,” and 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FD02F9700C4907C6" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[673,769,1665,1698]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Parantechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="apicalis">apicalis</taxonomicName>
formed a distinct group from other species of 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FF76F9590E2E07AD" box="[213,358,1704,1737]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Antechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Antechinus</taxonomicName>
. In light of this, M. Archer resurrected both of Tate’s genera, placing 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FF0DF9210E320795" authorityName="Spencer" authorityYear="1896" box="[174,378,1744,1777]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Phascogale" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macdonnellensis">macdonnellensis</taxonomicName>
and “ 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FE6FF9210D740795" box="[460,572,1744,1777]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Pseudantechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ningbing">ningbing</taxonomicName>
” under 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FD12F9210CCF0795" authorityName="Tate" authorityYear="1947" box="[689,903,1744,1777]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Pseudantechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudantechinus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FC6EF9210B6A0795" authorityName="Johnson" authorityYear="1954" box="[973,1058,1744,1777]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Antechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bilarni">bilarni</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FBCBF9210B800795" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[1128,1224,1744,1777]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Parantechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="apicalis">apicalis</taxonomicName>
under 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FA8FF9210E70067C" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Parantechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Parantechinus</taxonomicName>
. Direct sequencing of mtDNA and nDNA has been conducted over the last decade, resolving 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FE08F8EE0D090624" authorityName="Kitchener &amp; Caputi" authorityYear="1988" box="[427,577,1823,1856]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Pseudantechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="woolleyae">P. woolleyae</taxonomicName>
assister to all congeners, and 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FC52F8EE0BC00624" box="[1009,1160,1823,1856]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Pseudantechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ningbing">P. ningbing</taxonomicName>
was resolved as sister to a clade containing 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FD8EF8B70DF50603" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1906" box="[557,701,1862,1895]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Phascogale" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mimulus">P. mimulus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FD6EF8B70CF40603" authorityName="Spencer" authorityYear="1896" box="[717,956,1862,1895]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Phascogale" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macdonnellensis">P. macdonnellensis</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FBAAF8B70B2C0603" authorityName="Cooper, Aplin &amp; Adams" authorityYear="2000" box="[1033,1124,1862,1895]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Pseudantechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="roryi">P. roryi</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2AC3655CFFA42449FF08F8870DEF06B8" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" type="distribution">
<caption id="36A6665FFFA42449FF08F8870DEF06B8" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6608160" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6608160" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6608160/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" targetBox="[171,762,885,1299]" targetPageId="13">
<paragraph id="626636D7FFA42449FF08F8870DEF06B8" blockId="13.[168,1379,1319,3470]" pageId="13" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis id="50ADEAC5FFA42449FF08F8870E1306EB" bold="true" box="[171,347,1910,1935]" pageId="13" pageNumber="298">Distribution.</emphasis>
W Western Australia, across the Fortescue River Basin (
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FBDAF8870BAA06EB" box="[1145,1250,1910,1935]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Pilbara" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Pilbara</taxonomicName>
), W Ashburton, (Ashburton region), W one-half of Austin (Murchison region), and a single record from the Little Sandy Desert.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2AC3655CFFA42449FF08F8150A6708D2" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" type="description">
<paragraph id="626636D7FFA42449FF08F8150A6708D2" blockId="13.[168,1379,1319,3470]" pageId="13" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis id="50ADEAC5FFA42449FF08F8150EEC0961" bold="true" box="[171,420,2020,2053]" pageId="13" pageNumber="298">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 10.7-10.8 cm,tail 7.5-8.5 cm; weight 35-50 g (males) and 30-45 g (females). There is subtle sexual dimorphism for size. Fur of Woolley’s 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FF0FF7C30ED00937" authorityName="Tate" authorityYear="1947" box="[172,408,2098,2131]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Pseudantechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudantechinus</taxonomicName>
is rich brown above and buff below. There are chestnut patches behind ears. Tail is fattened at base. Once confused with both the Fat-tailed 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FB6BF7AB0E4F09C7" authorityName="Tate" authorityYear="1947" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Pseudantechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudantechinus</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FEBDF7770D4409C7" authorityName="Spencer" authorityYear="1896" box="[286,524,2182,2211]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Phascogale" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macdonnellensis">P. macdonnellensis</taxonomicName>
) and Rory’s 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FD63F7770CE409C7" authorityName="Tate" authorityYear="1947" box="[704,940,2182,2211]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Pseudantechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudantechinus</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FC61F7770B6C09C7" authorityName="Cooper, Aplin &amp; Adams" authorityYear="2000" box="[962,1060,2182,2211]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Pseudantechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="208" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="roryi">P. roryi</taxonomicName>
), Woolley’s 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FB6BF7770E4F09AD" authorityName="Tate" authorityYear="1947" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Pseudantechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudantechinus</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from them in having three upper premolar teeth, with the third having a crown area more than two-thirds that of the second premolar; usually three pairs of lower premolar teeth (although the third may be very small); and by accessory erectile tissue of males not forming an appendage to the penis. In hand, richer color of Woolley’s 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FE0BF6B70DDC0803" authorityName="Tate" authorityYear="1947" box="[424,660,2374,2407]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Pseudantechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudantechinus</taxonomicName>
(at least in specimens from the Murchison) is often distinctive. Woolley’s 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FE75F69C0D8A08EA" authorityName="Tate" authorityYear="1947" box="[470,706,2413,2446]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Pseudantechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudantechinus</taxonomicName>
(30-50 g) is also larger than Rory’s 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FB6BF69C0E4E08D2" authorityName="Tate" authorityYear="1947" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Pseudantechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudantechinus</taxonomicName>
(17-32 g), and these two species may co-occurin parts of their distributions.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2AC3655CFFA42449FF08F64D0B090DAD" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="626636D7FFA42449FF08F64D0B090DAD" blockId="13.[168,1379,1319,3470]" pageId="13" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis id="50ADEAC5FFA42449FF08F64D0E5008B9" bold="true" box="[171,280,2492,2525]" pageId="13" pageNumber="298">Habitat.</emphasis>
Apparently favors rocky habitats, in various vegetation associations. The distribution of Woolley’s Pseudantechinusis characterized by an arid climate with primarily summer rain and precipitation of 200-300 mm/year. Northern districts of Fortescue and Keartland have a tropical arid climate. Fortescue District has essentially tree and shrub-steppe communities of 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FDE0F5AB0D860B1F" box="[579,718,2650,2683]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Eucalyptus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Eucalyptus</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FD43F5AB0C380B1F" box="[736,880,2650,2683]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Myrtaceae</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FC62F5AB0B5F0B1F" box="[961,1047,2650,2683]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Acacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Acacia</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FB8AF5AB0BE30B1F" box="[1065,1195,2650,2683]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
) shrubs over 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FF0CF5700E0D0BC6" box="[175,325,2689,2722]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Triodia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">Triodia spp.</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FEFDF5700E9F0BC6" authorityName="Barnhart" authorityYear="1895" baseAuthorityName="R.Br." box="[350,471,2689,2722]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
). Keartland District is shrub steppe. Ashburton District, however, is almost entirely mulga (
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FDB3F5580D990BAE" box="[528,721,2729,2762]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Acacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aneura">Acacia aneura</taxonomicName>
). Austin District is predominantly mulga (
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FA87F5580F980B95" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Acacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Acacia</taxonomicName>
) low woodland on plains that reduce to scrub on hillsides and tree steppe of 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FA90F5210E190A7C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Eucalyptus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">Eucalyptus spp.</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FE06F5060DC80A7C" box="[421,640,2807,2840]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Triodia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="basedowii">Triodia basedowii</taxonomicName>
on sand plains. Soil structure and topography vary greatly among these districts; however, Fortescue District is a rugged, mountainous region, chiefly of hard alkaline red soils on plains and peds with shallow, skeletal soils on ranges. Ashburton and Austin districts are primarily shallow, earthy loams overlying redbrown hardpan, with shallow, stony loams, a feature of hills and ranges. One Woolley’s 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FF08F44D0EDE0AB9" authorityName="Tate" authorityYear="1947" box="[171,406,3004,3037]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Pseudantechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudantechinus</taxonomicName>
from Karlamilyi (= Rudall River) National Park in Keartland District was from a small, stony hill of brown,salty sand, featuring 50% stones. In addition to Woolley’s 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FE9BF3FA0D6B0D48" authorityName="Tate" authorityYear="1947" box="[312,547,3083,3116]" class="Mammalia" family="Dasyuridae" genus="Pseudantechinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dasyuromorphia" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudantechinus</taxonomicName>
occurring on small stony hills at Rudall River, it has been collected from gemstone-bearing country, granite-boulder country, and a rocky hillside; another specimen was captured in buffelgrass (
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FCE1F3AF0B590D1F" box="[834,1041,3166,3195]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Cenchrus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ciliaris">Cenchrus ciliaris</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="A5D94D54FFA42449FB82F3AF0BDB0D1F" authorityName="Barnhart" authorityYear="1895" baseAuthorityName="R.Br." box="[1057,1171,3166,3195]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
) on small saltflat plain. In a recent survey of the Little Sandy Desert (mid-Western Australia), five Woolley’s Pseudantechinuses were all caught on sandstone ranges.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2AC3655CFFA42449FF0AF33E0B250D94" box="[169,1133,3279,3312]" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" type="food_feeding">
