</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2AC3655CFFA42449FA08FDFD0683027E" pageId="13" pageNumber="298" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="626636D7FFA42449FA08FDFD0683027E" blockId="13.[1448,2656,287,917]" pageId="13" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis id="50ADEAC5FFA42449FA08FDFD08420349" bold="true" box="[1451,1802,524,557]" pageId="13" pageNumber="298">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The [UCN Red List. Woolley’s Pseudantechinus has a wide distribution and presumably a large overall population. It occurs in a number of protected areas and lacks any known major conservation threats. Woolley’s Pseudantechinus has been recorded from a number of protected areas (e.g. Barlee Range Nature Reserve, Karlamilyi or Rudall River National Park, and Millstream-Chichester National Park). Further studies are required to clarify distribution, abundance, natural history, and threats to Woolley’s Pseudantechinus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
